  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently positioned right at the GEX flip (6781 vs 6780.74 spot), creating a critical inflection point where any move above triggers systematic selling into strength while moves below activate buying support. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+67.6B) acts as a hard ceiling where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the 6770 negative gamma pocket (-18.6B) provides a meaningful support zone where dealers flip to buying dips. With spot sandwiched between dense positive gamma strikes (6780-6800 all showing +33B to +67B), expect heightened mean reversion behavior and range-bound action as dealers actively dampen volatility.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect tight, choppy trading between 6770-6800 with dealers capping both upside and downside moves.",
